('Grammar and Structure', 'Part of Speech', 'curious', 'What is the part of speech of \"curious\" in the sentence: \"The child was curious about the noise\"?', 'adjective', 'conjunction', 'interjection', 'preposition', '\"Curious\" describes the child’s state, so it is an adjective. It does not join ideas (conjunction), act as an exclamation (interjection), or show relationship (preposition).'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Part of Speech', 'curiously', 'What is the part of speech of \"curiously\" in the sentence: \"She glanced at the note curiously before opening it\"?', 'adverb', 'adjective', 'conjunction', 'interjection', '\"Curiously\" modifies the verb \"glanced,\" indicating manner, so it is an adverb. It does not describe a noun (adjective), join clauses (conjunction), or express an exclamation (interjection).'),
